xhuYOczKTm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reca7HEiPdstRWOnf","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reca7HEiPdstRWOnf","target":"recQ1bj3p4Lj5MYY6","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recadTUoEtsTKYgH7","ref":"Isa.27.1","text":"In that day the LORD with his sore and great and strong sword shall punish leviathan the piercing serpent, even leviathan that crooked serpent; and he shall slay the dragon that is in the sea.","year":-712},{"id":"recQ9zPYtyiBjB3pm","ref":"Isa.27.2","text":"In that day sing ye unto her, A vineyard of red wine.","year":-712},{"id":"recoPz3S4Zf0RpzMt","ref":"Isa.27.3","text":"I the LORD do keep it; I will water it every moment: lest any hurt it, I will keep it night and day.","year":-712},{"id":"recBbwySPd08c1nQo","ref":"Isa.27.4","text":"Fury is not in me: who would set the briers and thorns against me in battle? I would go through them, I would burn them together.","year":-712},{"id":"recDw6rKdT6j6dRQC","ref":"Isa.27.5","text":"Or let him take hold of my strength, that he may make peace with me; and he shall make peace with me.","year":-712},{"id":"recNwaNTNjkclVl8J","ref":"Isa.27.6","text":"He shall cause them that come of Jacob to take root: Israel shall blossom and bud, and fill the face of the world with fruit.","year":-712},{"id":"recPvdekWOF2fEaLY","ref":"Isa.27.7","text":"Hath he smitten him, as he smote those that smote him? or is he slain according to the slaughter of them that are slain by him?","year":-712},{"id":"recKh9mIUqsHy9WRp","ref":"Isa.27.8","text":"In measure, when it shooteth forth, thou wilt debate with it: he stayeth his rough wind in the day of the east wind.","year":-712}]}
